片名：《闪灵》

4
00:03:01,117 --> 00:03:03,601
面试

5
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:14,966
嗨 我跟乌尔曼先生约好了的
Hi. I've got an appointment with Mr. Ullman.

6
00:03:15,170 --> 00:03:17,104
我叫杰克.托兰斯
My name is Jack Torrance.

7
00:03:17,304 --> 00:03:19,829
在左边第一个门进去就是他办公室
His office is the first door on the left.

8
00:03:20,040 --> 00:03:21,268
谢谢
Thank you.

9
00:03:38,623 --> 00:03:39,487
乌尔曼先生?
Mr. Ullman?

10
00:03:39,691 --> 00:03:40,953
我是杰克.托兰斯
I'm Jack Torrance.

11
00:03:41,159 --> 00:03:43,127
快进来 杰克
Come on in, Jack.

12
00:03:44,229 --> 00:03:46,753
-很高兴见到你      -我也是
-Very nice to meet you.     -Nice to meet you.

13
00:03:46,964 --> 00:03:48,488
这是我的秘书 苏茜
This is my secretary, Susie.

14
00:03:48,899 --> 00:03:51,390
-苏茜 你好么?
-这地方不难找吧?
-Susie, how do you do?
-Any trouble finding us?

15
00:03:51,602 --> 00:03:54,435
很好找 我在路上花了三个半小时
No problem at all. I made the trip in 3 1/2 hours.

16
00:03:54,638 --> 00:03:56,537
不过旅途非常愉快
That's very good time.

17
00:03:56,873 --> 00:03:58,465
坐会吧 杰克
Sit down a minute, Jack.

18
00:03:58,708 --> 00:04:00,471
随便点
Just make yourself at home.

19
00:04:00,677 --> 00:04:01,939
要来点咖啡么?
Like some coffee?

20
00:04:02,145 --> 00:04:04,635
如果有的话就来点 谢谢
If you're having some, I wouldn't mind. Thanks.

21
00:04:04,847 --> 00:04:05,836
苏茜     好的
Susie.     Sure.

22
00:04:06,048 --> 00:04:07,777
去叫比尔.沃森过来
And ask Bill Watson to join us.

23
00:04:07,983 --> 00:04:09,416
好的 这就去
Yes, I will.

24
00:04:20,294 --> 00:04:21,420
妈妈
Mom?

25
00:04:22,296 --> 00:04:23,455
干吗
Yeah?

26
00:04:23,864 --> 00:04:27,493
你真的想整个冬天都呆在那间酒店里么?
Do you really want to go and live in that hotel for the winter?

27
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:29,466
当然啦
Sure I do.

28
00:04:29,669 --> 00:04:31,603
会很好玩的
It'll be lots of fun.

29
00:04:33,472 --> 00:04:35,565
是的 我想也是
Yeah. I guess so.

30
00:04:35,775 --> 00:04:39,939
不过 那里肯定没什么人跟我一起玩了
Anyway, there's hardly anybody to play with around here.

31
00:04:40,746 --> 00:04:44,237
我知道 反正你也不怎么去交新朋友
I know. It always takes a little time to make new friends.

32
00:04:45,850 --> 00:04:48,148
是的 我觉得也是
Yeah, I guess so.

33
00:04:48,920 --> 00:04:49,944
托尼怎么样了
What about Tony?

34
00:04:50,155 --> 00:04:52,418
我打赌他肯定很向往去酒店住
He's looking forward to the hotel, I bet.

35
00:04:53,090 --> 00:04:55,456
不 我不想呢 托兰斯夫人
No, I ain't, Mrs. Torrance.

36
00:04:55,859 --> 00:04:58,157
好了 别这样 托尼 别傻了
Now, come on, Tony. Don't be silly.

37
00:04:58,695 --> 00:05:00,526
我不想去
I don't want to go there.

38
00:05:01,164 --> 00:05:03,098
你怎么会不想去呢?
How come you don't want to go?

39
00:05:03,432 --> 00:05:05,332
我就是不想去
I just don't.

40
00:05:05,601 --> 00:05:08,399
在丹佛 他们有告诉过你
Did they give you any idea in Denver...

41
00:05:08,604 --> 00:05:10,264
具体的工作职责么?
...about what the job entails?

42
00:05:10,472 --> 00:05:12,565
只是总体上讲了一下
Only in a very general way.

43
00:05:15,043 --> 00:05:17,637
这儿的冬天会非常的可怕
The winters can be fantastically cruel.

44
00:05:17,846 --> 00:05:21,303
基本上来说 你的工作就是要防止可能发生的
The basic idea is to cope with the very costly damage...

45
00:05:21,515 --> 00:05:23,506
重大损失和破坏
...and depreciation which can occur.

46
00:05:23,717 --> 00:05:26,151
其中包括要开动汽锅
This consists mainly of running the boiler...

47
00:05:26,353 --> 00:05:30,311
每天轮流给酒店的不同部分送热
...heating different parts of the hotel on a daily rotating basis...

48
00:05:30,523 --> 00:05:33,048
并在出现损坏的时候进行维修工作
...repairing damage as it occurs...

49
00:05:33,259 --> 00:05:36,251
并且做好维护工作 别让大自然把这儿毁了
...and doing repairs so the elements can't get a foothold.

50
00:05:37,330 --> 00:05:39,490
我觉得应该没问题
That sounds fine to me.

51
00:05:39,965 --> 00:05:42,934
就身体方面来说 这工作并不难
Physically, it's not a very demanding job.

52
00:05:43,135 --> 00:05:46,298
唯一让人觉得难受的就是这儿的冬天
The only thing that can get a bit trying here during the winter...

53
00:05:46,471 --> 00:05:48,961
会让你觉得孤独难耐
...is a tremendous sense of isolation.

54
00:05:50,241 --> 00:05:54,803
这正是我想要的
That just happens to be exactly what I'm looking for.

55
00:05:55,146 --> 00:05:58,273
我正在构思一本新书
I'm outlining a new writing project.

56
00:05:58,582 --> 00:06:01,881
五个月的平静正是我想要的
Five months of peace is just what I want.

57
00:06:02,652 --> 00:06:04,381
那就太好了 杰克
That's very good, Jack.

58
00:06:04,688 --> 00:06:07,850
因为 对有些人来说
Because, for some people...

59
00:06:08,057 --> 00:06:09,820
孤独
solitude

60
00:06:10,025 --> 00:06:11,652
和与世隔绝
and isolation

61
00:06:12,528 --> 00:06:14,792
本身可能就是个大问题
...can, of itself, become a problem.

62
00:06:15,598 --> 00:06:17,189
对我来说不是的
Not for me.

63
00:06:17,732 --> 00:06:20,963
那你的妻子和儿子呢?
他们能受得了么?
How about your wife and son?
Do you think they'll take to it?

64
00:06:22,770 --> 00:06:23,930
他们也会很喜欢的
They'll love it.

65
00:06:24,138 --> 00:06:25,332
太好了
Great.

66
00:06:28,242 --> 00:06:31,473
在比尔带你去熟悉环境之前
Before I turn you over to Bill...

67
00:06:31,678 --> 00:06:35,169
我想还有件事情我们得谈谈
there's one other thing I think we should talk about.

68
00:06:35,381 --> 00:06:36,814
并不是想搞得很戏剧性
Not to sound melodramatic...

69
00:06:37,016 --> 00:06:39,576
但是 知道这件事情会让某些人
...but it's been known to give a few people...

70
00:06:39,785 --> 00:06:41,980
对这份工作有所迟疑的
...second thoughts about the job.

71
00:06:42,688 --> 00:06:44,348
你勾起了我的好奇心
I'm intrigued.

72
00:06:44,556 --> 00:06:46,888
我想他们在丹佛并没有跟你说过
I don't suppose they said anything in Denver...

73
00:06:47,092 --> 00:06:51,051
在一九七零年这儿发生过桩悲剧
...about the tragedy we had up here during the winter of 1970.

74
00:06:51,663 --> 00:06:53,653
他们确实没有提起过
I don't believe they did.

75
00:06:56,233 --> 00:06:57,928
以前干我这个职位的前辈
My predecessor in this job...

76
00:06:58,669 --> 00:07:01,900
雇了一个叫查尔斯.格兰蒂的人做冬季看守
...hired a man named Charles Grady as the winter caretaker.

77
00:07:02,106 --> 00:07:05,632
他和他的妻子以及两个女儿 一个八岁 一个十岁
He came up with his wife and 2 little girls of about 8 and 10.

78
00:07:05,842 --> 00:07:08,834
他的履历非常好 而且倍受推崇
He had a good employment record, good references.

79
00:07:09,045 --> 00:07:11,309
就我所知 他好像
And from what I've been told, he seemed...

80
00:07:11,514 --> 00:07:14,209
看起来是个绝对正常的人
...like a completely normal individual.

81
00:07:14,416 --> 00:07:16,782
但是 就在那年冬天某个时候
But at some point during the winter...

82
00:07:16,985 --> 00:07:20,614
他好像是彻底精神崩溃了
he must have suffered some kind of a complete mental breakdown.

83
00:07:20,822 --> 00:07:23,187
就疯了
He ran amuck...

84
00:07:26,594 --> 00:07:28,789
拿斧头砍死了自己的家人
...and killed his family with an ax.

85
00:07:30,064 --> 00:07:34,693
然后把他们整洁得放在西翼的一间房里
Stacked them neatly in a room in the west wing

86
00:07:35,502 --> 00:07:39,199
之后 就吞枪自杀了
and then... he put both barrels of his shotgun in his mouth.

87
00:07:40,440 --> 00:07:42,236
警方认为
The police thought...

88
00:07:42,441 --> 00:07:46,502
他就是患上了以前所说的幽居病
...that it was what the old-timers used to call cabin fever.

89
00:07:46,712 --> 00:07:49,738
如果人们长时间被关在某一地方
A kind of claustrophobic reaction which can occur...

90
00:07:49,949 --> 00:07:54,078
就会产生这种幽居恐惧症
when people are shut in together over long periods of time.

91
00:07:59,157 --> 00:08:00,589
这真是
That is...

92
00:08:00,791 --> 00:08:02,315
够戏剧性的了
...quite a story.

93
00:08:03,627 --> 00:08:05,094
是的 确实
Yeah, it is.

94
00:08:06,196 --> 00:08:09,494
我还是很难相信这儿发生过这种事
It's still hard for me to believe it actually happened here.

95
00:08:09,832 --> 00:08:11,527
不过确实发生过
But it did.

96
00:08:13,302 --> 00:08:17,329
我想你能理解我告诉你这件事的原因
I think you can appreciate why I wanted to tell you about it.

97
00:08:17,873 --> 00:08:20,363
当然
I certainly can.

98
00:08:20,875 --> 00:08:23,435
而且我也明白为什么你在丹佛的同事
I also understand why your people in Denver...

99
00:08:23,645 --> 00:08:25,909
会留给你来告诉我这件事
...left it for you to tell me.

100
00:08:27,115 --> 00:08:29,810
很显然 有些人会因为这地方
Obviously, some people can be put off...

101
00:08:30,017 --> 00:08:34,113
发生过那种事而退缩的
from staying in a place where something like that happened.

102
00:08:34,321 --> 00:08:39,223
您大可放心 这种事不会发生在我身上的
You can rest assured that's not going to happen with me.

103
00:08:39,425 --> 00:08:43,088
至于我妻子的话
And as far as my wife is concerned...

104
00:08:43,296 --> 00:08:47,129
我肯定她听到这事会无比兴奋的
...I'm sure she'll be absolutely fascinated when I tell her.

105
00:08:47,332 --> 00:08:50,165
她对鬼故事
She's a confirmed ghost story...

106
00:08:50,369 --> 00:08:52,803
和恐怖电影非常着迷
...and horror film addict.

107
00:08:57,641 --> 00:09:01,338
托尼 你觉得爸爸会得到这份工作么?
Tony, do you think Dad'll get the job?

108
00:09:02,747 --> 00:09:04,942
他已经得到了
He already did.

109
00:09:05,382 --> 00:09:09,113
过几分钟 他就会打电话来告诉温蒂了
He 's going to phone Wendy up in a few minutes to tell her.

110
00:09:23,832 --> 00:09:26,493
嗨 宝贝    嗨 亲爱的怎么样了?
Hi, babe.  Hi, hon. How's it going?

111
00:09:26,701 --> 00:09:30,296
太好了 我已经在酒店了还有很多事得做
Great. I'm at the hotel and I still have a lot to go through.

112
00:09:30,505 --> 00:09:33,632
我想可能九点十点都回不来的了
I don't think I can get home before 9:00 or 10:00.

113
00:09:33,840 --> 00:09:35,330
看来你好像是得到这份工作了
Sounds like you got the job.

114
00:09:35,542 --> 00:09:38,238
是的 这儿很美
Right. It's a beautiful place.

115
00:09:38,445 --> 00:09:40,572
你和丹尼肯定会喜欢这儿的
You and Danny are going to love it.

116
00:09:42,049 --> 00:09:44,949
托尼 你为什么不想去酒店?
Tony, why don't you want to go to the hotel?

117
00:09:45,217 --> 00:09:46,946
我不知道
I don't know.

118
00:09:48,020 --> 00:09:51,547
你肯定知道 现在 快点告诉我吧
You do too know. Now come on, tell me.

119
00:09:52,124 --> 00:09:54,182
我不想说
I don't want to.

120
00:09:54,893 --> 00:09:56,155
求你了
Please.

121
00:09:57,395 --> 00:09:58,521
不
No.

122
00:09:58,830 --> 00:10:00,923
来吧 托尼 告诉我吧
Now, Tony, tell me.

123
00:10:58,082 --> 00:11:02,246
我们肯定已经上到很高的地方了
空气都完全不同的呢
We must really be high up.
The air feels so different.

124
00:11:07,891 --> 00:11:09,119
爸爸
Dad?

125
00:11:11,928 --> 00:11:13,623
我饿了
I'm hungry.

126
00:11:15,465 --> 00:11:18,194
你应该把早餐吃了的
You should've eaten your breakfast.

127
00:11:19,034 --> 00:11:21,935
我们一到酒店就给你弄点东西吃 好么?
We'll get you something as soon as we get to the hotel.

128
00:11:22,138 --> 00:11:23,765
好的 妈妈
Okay, Mom.

129
00:11:25,207 --> 00:11:29,336
这不就是当纳聚会受风雪围困的地方么?
Wasn't it around here that the Donner party got snowbound?

130
00:11:31,079 --> 00:11:34,571
我想应该还要再往西点 在深山里
I think that was farther west, in the Sierras.

131
00:11:36,049 --> 00:11:38,483
什么是当纳聚会呀?
What was the Donner party?

132
00:11:40,420 --> 00:11:44,686
是指还在使用马车的年代的一群拓荒者
They were a party of settlers in covered wagon times.

133
00:11:44,925 --> 00:11:48,189
在某个冬天被风雪围困在了山里
They got snowbound one winter in the mountains.

134
00:11:48,394 --> 00:11:52,592
他们不得不嗜食同类以生存下去
They had to resort to cannibalism in order to stay alive.

135
00:11:53,733 --> 00:11:56,633
你是说人吃人?
You mean they ate each other up?

136
00:11:56,835 --> 00:11:59,929
为了生存 他们不得不这么做
They had to in order to survive.

137
00:12:00,138 --> 00:12:01,366
杰克
Jack.

138
00:12:01,573 --> 00:12:02,665
别担心 妈妈
Don't worry, Mom.

139
00:12:02,874 --> 00:12:07,207
我知道人吃人的事 电视里都有播
I know all about cannibalism. I saw it on TV.

140
00:12:07,411 --> 00:12:10,039
看吧 没事的
See, it's okay.

141
00:12:10,247 --> 00:12:12,681
他都在电视上看过了
He saw it all on the television.

142
00:12:43,376 --> 00:12:45,207
飞机几点起飞     八点半
What time does the plane leave?   8:30.

143
00:12:45,412 --> 00:12:48,176
那我们就有足够的时间来收拾东西
That gives us plenty of time to go over everything.

144
00:12:48,381 --> 00:12:50,315
再见 乌尔曼先生    再见
Goodbye, Mr. Ullman.     Bye.

145
00:12:50,517 --> 00:12:53,644
早上好 我希望你们没有等得太久
Good morning. I hope you haven't been waiting too long.

146
00:12:53,852 --> 00:12:56,480
没关系 我们有时间来吃点东西
No problem. We had time to grab a bite to eat.

147
00:12:56,689 --> 00:12:59,590
很好 很高兴你在厨房关闭之前到达了
Good. Glad you made it before they shut down the kitchen.

148
00:12:59,792 --> 00:13:01,520
你的家人四处参观去了?
Is your family having a look around?

149
00:13:01,726 --> 00:13:05,093
还没呢 我儿子发现了游戏室
No, my son's discovered the games room.

150
00:13:05,296 --> 00:13:08,390
你们的行李拿进来了么?      都在那儿了
Has your luggage been brought in?   Right there.

151
00:13:08,967 --> 00:13:10,934
由于我们得在今天搞定一切
In view of all we have to cover today...

152
00:13:11,134 --> 00:13:14,797
我想我们还是快去看看你们的房间 开始工作
l suggest we have a quick look at your apartment and get started.

153
00:13:15,005 --> 00:13:17,769
把托兰斯的行李送到他们的房间去
Have the Torrances' things brought to their apartment.

154
00:13:17,975 --> 00:13:20,670
我得先把我的家人都找回来
I'd better collect my family first.

155
00:13:28,817 --> 00:13:31,183
这是科罗拉多休闲室
This is our Colorado Lounge.

156
00:13:31,386 --> 00:13:33,820
真漂亮
It's beautiful.

157
00:13:34,222 --> 00:13:36,087
天哪
My God!

158
00:13:36,291 --> 00:13:38,850
这地方真棒 对吧 亲爱的
This place is fantastic, isn't it, hon?

159
00:13:39,059 --> 00:13:40,390
当然
It sure is.

160
00:14:33,309 --> 00:14:35,868
这是酒店的员工翼
This is the staff wing of the hotel.

161
00:14:36,844 --> 00:14:40,177
冬季其它房间都不会供热
None of the other bedrooms are heated during the winter.

162
00:14:40,415 --> 00:14:43,316
再见 乌尔曼先生     再见 姑娘们
Goodbye, Mr. Ullman.    Goodbye, girls.

163
00:14:43,551 --> 00:14:45,541
这儿就是你们的住处
And here are your quarters.

164
00:14:45,952 --> 00:14:48,546
客厅 卧室 洗手间
Living room, bedroom, bathroom.

165
00:14:48,755 --> 00:14:51,246
这间小卧室是你儿子的
And a small bedroom for your son.

166
00:14:54,860 --> 00:14:56,885
给孩子住恰倒好处
Perfect for a child.

167
00:15:05,437 --> 00:15:07,530
远望酒店是什么时候修建的?
When was the Overlook built?

168
00:15:08,540 --> 00:15:10,770
一九零七年始建
Construction started in 1907.

169
00:15:10,975 --> 00:15:12,942
一九零九年才完工
It was finished in 1909.

170
00:15:13,143 --> 00:15:15,805
这地方本来是印第安坟场
The site's supposed to be on an Indian burial ground.

171
00:15:16,013 --> 00:15:17,640
所以在修建期间
They actually had to repel...

172
00:15:17,848 --> 00:15:20,749
还击退了几次印第安人的袭击
...a few Indian attacks as they were building it.

173
00:15:21,351 --> 00:15:23,251
那是雪地车
That's our Snowcat.

174
00:15:23,953 --> 00:15:25,978
-你们俩都会开车吧  -是的
-Can you both drive a car?  -Yes.

175
00:15:26,522 --> 00:15:30,083
很好 基本上雪地车的操作跟汽车差不多
That's fine. Basically the Snowcat operates very much like a car.

176
00:15:30,293 --> 00:15:32,021
用不了多久你们就能熟练操作的了
It won't take you long to get the hang of it.

177
00:15:32,794 --> 00:15:34,421
这就是厨房么 哈?
This is the kitchen, huh?

178
00:15:34,629 --> 00:15:36,221
是的
This is it.

179
00:15:36,431 --> 00:15:39,366
你喜欢么 丹尼? 对你来说够大了么?
How do you like it, Danny? Is it big enough for you?

180
00:15:40,201 --> 00:15:42,396
是我见过最大的厨房了
It's the biggest place I ever seen.

181
00:15:42,636 --> 00:15:44,968
这地方就跟个迷宫似的
This whole place is such an enormous maze.

182
00:15:45,172 --> 00:15:48,733
估计我每次进来都得撒面包屑做标记
I'll have to leave a trail of breadcrumbs every time I come in.

183
00:15:49,642 --> 00:15:51,507
别让它把你吓坏了
Don't let it get you down.

184
00:15:51,711 --> 00:15:54,202
这儿再大也不过就是个厨房而已
It's big, but it ain't nothing but a kitchen.

185
00:15:54,414 --> 00:15:56,609
有很多东西你根本就不需要碰
A lot of this stuff you'll never have to touch.

186
00:15:56,816 --> 00:15:59,045
就算碰了 我也不知道该怎么弄
I wouldn't know what to do with it if I did.

187
00:15:59,251 --> 00:16:02,379
有一件事情是肯定的 就是你不用为吃的担心
One thing for sure, you don't have to worry about food.

188
00:16:02,588 --> 00:16:07,252
你们能在这儿吃上一年
而且还每天都能吃到不同的菜色
You folks could eat here for a year
and never have the same menu twice.

189
00:16:07,459 --> 00:16:10,552
这是小型冷藏间
Right here is our walk-in freezer.

190
00:16:11,696 --> 00:16:14,756
所有的肉都冷藏在这里面
This is where we keep all of our meat.

191
00:16:14,966 --> 00:16:16,957
十五条烟熏肋骨
You got 15 rib roasts...

192
00:16:17,168 --> 00:16:19,294
三十袋十镑一袋的碎牛肉
...30 ten-pound bags of hamburger.

193
00:16:19,503 --> 00:16:22,563
十二只火鸡 大约四十只小鸡
We got 12 turkeys, about 40 chickens...

194
00:16:22,773 --> 00:16:25,867
五十个腰肉牛排 两打烟熏猪肉
...50 sirloin steaks, two dozen of pork roast...

195
00:16:26,076 --> 00:16:29,044
二十条羔羊腿 你喜欢羔羊肉么 医生?
-不.
...and 20 legs of lamb. Do you like lamb, Doc?
-No.

196
00:16:30,279 --> 00:16:32,645
不喜欢? 那你最喜欢吃什么呢?
You don't? What's your favorite food, then?

197
00:16:32,848 --> 00:16:34,713
炸薯条加番茄酱
French fries and ketchup.

198
00:16:35,451 --> 00:16:37,441
我想我们也能弄出那玩意来吃的 医生
I think we can manage that too, Doc.

199
00:16:37,652 --> 00:16:39,381
现在过这边来 小心脚下
Come along, now. Watch your step.

200
00:16:46,126 --> 00:16:47,684
哈罗朗先生 你怎么知道我们叫他医生?
How'd you know we call him Doc?

201
00:16:47,895 --> 00:16:51,922
-抱歉
-医生 你叫了丹尼两次医生
-Beg your pardon?
Doc. You called Danny "Doc" twice.

202
00:16:52,132 --> 00:16:53,531
我有么？
I did?

203
00:16:54,334 --> 00:16:57,461
我们有时叫他医生 就像兔巴哥卡通里一样
We call him Doc sometimes, like in the Bugs Bunny cartoons.

204
00:16:57,670 --> 00:16:58,932
不过 你是怎么知道的呢
But how did you know?

205
00:16:59,138 --> 00:17:01,663
我想我可能是听到你这么叫他了
I guess I probably heard you call him that.

206
00:17:01,874 --> 00:17:04,138
有可能 不过 老实说 我确实不记得
It's possible. But I honestly don't remember...

207
00:17:04,343 --> 00:17:06,537
在见到你之后 有那样叫过他
...calling him that since we've been with you.

208
00:17:06,745 --> 00:17:08,940
不管怎样 他看起来就像是个医生 不是么?
Anyway, he looks like a Doc, doesn't he?

209
00:17:10,382 --> 00:17:11,815
你好么 医生?
What's up, Doc?

210
00:17:13,652 --> 00:17:15,846
这是间库房
Now, this is the storeroom.

211
00:17:17,588 --> 00:17:19,419
所有的干货和罐装食物
In here is where we keep...

212
00:17:19,623 --> 00:17:22,421
都储藏在这儿
...all the dried goods and the canned goods.

213
00:17:22,626 --> 00:17:25,059
有水果罐头 蔬菜罐头
We got canned fruits and vegetables...

214
00:17:25,261 --> 00:17:29,061
鱼罐头 肉罐头 冷热水冲调的谷物
...canned fish and meats, hot and cold cereals.

215
00:17:29,265 --> 00:17:32,462
烤面包片 玉米片 泡芙
Post Toasties, Corn Flakes, Sugar Puffs...

216
00:17:32,669 --> 00:17:36,695
萨琪玛 燕麦片 小麦 还有麦乳
Rice Krispies, oatmeal, Wheatena and Cream of Wheat.

217
00:17:36,939 --> 00:17:39,373
还有十二壶蜜糖
You got a dozen jugs of black molasses.

218
00:17:39,575 --> 00:17:42,771
六十盒干奶
We got 60 boxes of dried milk...

219
00:17:50,418 --> 00:17:52,885
来点冰淇淋怎么样 医生?
How'd you like some ice cream, Doc?

220
00:17:55,288 --> 00:17:57,279
各种小吃 甜点
Sociables, finger rolls...

221
00:17:57,491 --> 00:17:59,015
要什么有什么
...and 7 kinds of what have you.

222
00:17:59,226 --> 00:18:02,752
这边还有桃干杏干
Now, we've got dried peaches, dried apricots...

223
00:18:02,962 --> 00:18:06,056
葡萄干还有洋李干
...dried raisins and dried prunes.

224
00:18:06,265 --> 00:18:10,564
你知道的 要想过得轻松开心点就得把一切都弄清楚
You know, you got to keep regular if you want to be happy.

225
00:18:13,471 --> 00:18:15,098
怎么样了?     很好
How're you getting on?     Fine.

226
00:18:15,306 --> 00:18:18,867
能把托兰斯夫人借我们用用不?
我们要去地下室看看
Can we borrow Mrs. Torrance?
We're on our way to the basement.

227
00:18:19,077 --> 00:18:21,010
我保证不会很久的
I promise we won't keep her very long.

228
00:18:21,211 --> 00:18:24,408
没问题 乌尔曼先生 我正要去拿冰淇淋呢
No problem, Mr. Ullman. I was just getting to the ice cream.

229
00:18:24,615 --> 00:18:26,480
要来点冰淇淋么 医生?     好的
You like ice cream, Doc?     Yes.

230
00:18:27,351 --> 00:18:28,318
我就知道你想吃
I thought you did.

231
00:18:28,519 --> 00:18:31,578
在你们回来之前 不介意我带丹尼去吃点冰淇淋吧?
You folks mind if I give Danny some ice cream while we wait?

232
00:18:31,787 --> 00:18:33,618
当然不     我们不介意
Not at all.     We don't mind.

233
00:18:33,823 --> 00:18:36,018
很好     你觉得怎么样 医生?
Good.     Sound good to you, Doc?

234
00:18:36,225 --> 00:18:38,284
好的 要乖点哟
Okay, you behave yourself.

235
00:18:41,296 --> 00:18:43,161
你喜欢吃哪种冰淇淋呢
What kind of ice cream do you like?

236
00:18:43,365 --> 00:18:44,263
巧克力的
Chocolate.

237
00:18:44,466 --> 00:18:47,435
巧克力的 没问题 来吧 孩子
Chocolate it shall be. Come on, son.

238
00:18:52,006 --> 00:18:53,997
今天真是太充实了
It's amazing, all this activity today.

239
00:18:54,208 --> 00:18:57,006
住客和一些员工昨天就走了 不过
The guests and some staff left yesterday, but the...

240
00:18:57,211 --> 00:18:58,643
最后一天总是让人很忙乱
...last day's always hectic.

241
00:18:58,845 --> 00:19:01,905
人人都想尽早离开
Everybody wants to be on their way as early as possible.

242
00:19:02,115 --> 00:19:06,142
到今天下午五点 这儿就跟没人来过一样
By 5:00 tonight, you'll never know anybody was ever here.

243
00:19:06,352 --> 00:19:08,410
就跟间鬼店一样 哈?
Just like a ghost ship, huh?

244
00:19:14,092 --> 00:19:17,060
你知道我怎么知道你叫医生的么?
Do you know how I knew your name was Doc?

245
00:19:23,634 --> 00:19:26,033
你知道我在说什么 对吧?
You know what I'm talking about, don't you?

246
00:19:33,009 --> 00:19:36,500
我记得自己还是个孩子的时候
I can remember when I was a little boy...

247
00:19:36,912 --> 00:19:39,437
我和我奶奶可以
my grandmother and I could hold conversations

248
00:19:39,648 --> 00:19:43,482
不张嘴就聊天
entirely without ever opening our mouths.

249
00:19:44,553 --> 00:19:46,850
她把这叫做闪灵
She called it "shining."

250
00:19:48,356 --> 00:19:51,086
很长一段时间 我都觉得只有我们俩会
And for a long time I thought it was just the two of us...

251
00:19:51,292 --> 00:19:53,817
才拥有这种闪灵交流
...that had "the shine" to us.

252
00:19:54,528 --> 00:19:57,520
正如你可能认为只有你一个人一样
Just like you probably thought you was the only one.

253
00:19:58,198 --> 00:20:00,063
不过 还有的人也跟我们一样
But there are other folks...

254
00:20:00,267 --> 00:20:03,997
尽管他们大多不知道 或者是不相信
though mostly they don't know it, or don't believe it.

255
00:20:08,674 --> 00:20:11,108
你有这种能力多长时间了?
How long have you been able to do it?

256
00:20:16,314 --> 00:20:18,714
你为什么不想说这个?
Why don't you want to talk about it?

257
00:20:23,954 --> 00:20:26,013
我不能说的
I'm not supposed to.

258
00:20:27,591 --> 00:20:30,116
谁说你不能说
Who says you ain't supposed to?

259
00:20:33,563 --> 00:20:34,962
托尼
Tony.

260
00:20:36,933 --> 00:20:38,594
谁是托尼?
Who's Tony?

261
00:20:41,069 --> 00:20:44,470
托尼是住在我嘴里的小男孩
Tony's the little boy that lives in my mouth.

262
00:20:46,408 --> 00:20:48,433
托尼就是那个
Is Tony the one that...

263
00:20:48,644 --> 00:20:50,202
告诉你某些事情的人?     是的
...tells you things?     Yes.

264
00:20:54,749 --> 00:20:57,115
他怎么告诉你这些事情的？
How does he tell you the thing?

265
00:20:58,953 --> 00:21:03,252
就像是我睡觉的时候 他就给我看
It's like I go to sleep, and he shows me things.

266
00:21:03,456 --> 00:21:07,552
但是等我醒过来 并不记得所有的事情
But when I wake up, I can't remember everything.

267
00:21:09,395 --> 00:21:13,092
你爸爸妈妈知道托尼的事么?
Does your mom and dad know about Tony?

268
00:21:16,402 --> 00:21:18,961
他们知道他会告诉你些事情么?
Do they know he tells you things?

269
00:21:19,837 --> 00:21:22,772
托尼叫我绝不能告诉他们
Tony told me never to tell them.

270
00:21:24,909 --> 00:21:28,275
托尼有没有跟你提过这地方的事?
Has Tony ever told you anything about this place?

271
00:21:28,478 --> 00:21:31,038
关于远望酒店么?
About the Overlook Hotel?

272
00:21:34,317 --> 00:21:35,875
我不知道
I don't know.

273
00:21:36,787 --> 00:21:40,813
现在 好好想想 医生.  想想看.
Now think real hard, Doc. Think.

274
00:21:46,095 --> 00:21:48,494
这儿有些坏东西么?
Is there something bad here?

275
00:22:00,107 --> 00:22:02,541
你知道么 医生 如果有事发生的话
You know, Doc, when something happens...

276
00:22:02,743 --> 00:22:06,371
都会遗留下可寻的线索
it can leave a trace of itself behind.

277
00:22:07,146 --> 00:22:08,704
你看 就像
Say, like...

278
00:22:08,915 --> 00:22:11,975
某人是不是烤糊了面包片
...if someone burns toast.

279
00:22:14,087 --> 00:22:18,750
或许其他事情还会留下其他一些线索
Maybe things that happen leave other kind of traces behind.

280
00:22:19,925 --> 00:22:23,361
而那些线索并不是任何人都能发现的
Not things that anyone can notice.

281
00:22:23,562 --> 00:22:28,362
但却是拥有闪灵能力的人能看得见的
But things that people who shine can see.

282
00:22:29,467 --> 00:22:32,766
就像他们能看到还未发生的事情
Just like they can see things that haven't happened yet...

283
00:22:35,038 --> 00:22:39,202
有时又能看到很久之前发生过的事情
sometimes they can see things that happened a long time ago.

284
00:22:40,744 --> 00:22:43,610
我想这些年 在这间酒店
I think a lot of things happened right here...

285
00:22:43,812 --> 00:22:47,509
发生了很多事情
in this particular hotel over the years.

286
00:22:48,050 --> 00:22:50,450
而且发生的并不都是好事
And not all of them was good.

287
00:22:53,755 --> 00:22:56,383
二三七号房怎么回事呢?
What about room 237?

288
00:22:59,727 --> 00:23:01,922
二三七号房?
Room 237?

289
00:23:03,230 --> 00:23:06,324
你害怕二三七号房 是么?
You're scared of room 237, ain't you?

290
00:23:08,101 --> 00:23:09,568
不 我不怕
No, I ain't.

291
00:23:11,071 --> 00:23:14,904
哈罗朗先生 二三七号房里有什么吗?
Mr. Hallorann, what is in room 237?

292
00:23:16,242 --> 00:23:17,607
没什么
Nothing.

293
00:23:18,043 --> 00:23:21,273
二三七号房里什么都没有
There ain't nothing in room 237.

294
00:23:21,479 --> 00:23:24,710
不过 你要没事可千万别去那儿
But you ain't got no business going in there anyway.

295
00:23:24,916 --> 00:23:27,043
离那房间远点
So stay out.

296
00:23:27,252 --> 00:23:29,743
明白么? 离那儿远点
You understand? Stay out!

297
00:24:45,988 --> 00:24:47,717
早上好 亲爱的
Good morning, hon.

298
00:24:49,725 --> 00:24:51,488
早饭准备好了
Your breakfast is ready.

299
00:24:52,261 --> 00:24:53,888
现在几点了?
What time is it?

300
00:24:54,096 --> 00:24:55,960
大概十一点半了
It's about 11:30.

301
00:24:57,866 --> 00:24:59,458
十一点半了 天哪
11:30. Jesus.

302
00:25:00,401 --> 00:25:02,835
我想昨天晚上是熬得太晚了
I guess we've been staying up too late.

303
00:25:03,137 --> 00:25:04,569
我知道
I know it.

304
00:25:05,873 --> 00:25:08,740
我都照你喜欢的口味做的 单面的煎蛋
I made them just the way you like them, sunny-side up.

305
00:25:09,042 --> 00:25:10,600
很好
Nice.

306
00:25:12,880 --> 00:25:14,676
外面真是够漂亮的
It's really pretty outside.

307
00:25:14,881 --> 00:25:18,112
吃完早餐跟我一起去散散步怎么样?
How about taking me for a walk after you finish your breakfast?

308
00:25:18,718 --> 00:25:23,051
我想我应该先写点东西
I suppose I ought to try to do some writing first.

309
00:25:24,489 --> 00:25:26,150
有灵感了么?
Any ideas yet?

310
00:25:27,158 --> 00:25:28,819
灵感倒是不少
Lots of ideas.

311
00:25:29,027 --> 00:25:30,551
就是没一个好的
No good ones.

312
00:25:31,029 --> 00:25:33,496
一切都会好的
Something will come.

313
00:25:33,998 --> 00:25:37,934
只是得养成每天都进行写作的习惯
It's just a matter of settling into the habit of writing every day.

314
00:25:39,503 --> 00:25:41,198
就是这样
That's all it is.

315
00:26:00,555 --> 00:26:03,114
好的     你输定了
All right.     And you're going to lose.

316
00:26:03,324 --> 00:26:06,452
我会抓住你的 你最好跑快点
And I'm going to get you. You'd better run fast!

317
00:26:11,464 --> 00:26:12,590
小心
Look out!

318
00:26:12,799 --> 00:26:14,664
我来啦
I'm coming in close.

319
00:26:14,868 --> 00:26:17,359
输了的要去做清洁哟
Loser has to keep America clean.

320
00:26:17,604 --> 00:26:19,231
做清洁哟
Keep America clean.

321
00:26:20,239 --> 00:26:21,706
丹尼 你赢了
Danny, you win.

322
00:26:22,041 --> 00:26:24,373
我们还是用走的吧
Let's take the rest of this walking.

323
00:26:26,912 --> 00:26:28,311
把手给我
Give me your hand.

324
00:26:30,949 --> 00:26:32,746
漂亮吧?     是的
Isn't it beautiful?   Yes.

325
00:26:50,499 --> 00:26:51,864
死路
Dead end.

326
00:27:49,319 --> 00:27:50,946
我们走出来了
We made it.

327
00:27:51,454 --> 00:27:52,682
漂亮吧?
Isn't it beautiful?

328
00:28:14,374 --> 00:28:16,205
确实很漂亮
It's so pretty.

329
00:28:20,781 --> 00:28:23,749
我可没想到有这么大呢 你呢?   没呢
I didn't think it was going to be this big. Did you?   No.

330
00:31:01,723 --> 00:31:03,156
嗨 亲爱的
Hi, hon.

331
00:31:06,762 --> 00:31:08,161
怎么样了?
How's it going?

332
00:31:10,732 --> 00:31:11,891
很好
Fine.

333
00:31:14,001 --> 00:31:15,559
今天写了很多东西吧    是的
Get a lot written today?      Yes.

334
00:31:22,609 --> 00:31:25,169
很好 天气预报说今天会下雪呢
Good. The weather forecast said it's going to snow tonight.

335
00:31:30,382 --> 00:31:32,714
你想让我怎么对付暴风雪呢?
What do you want me to do about it?

336
00:31:34,853 --> 00:31:37,014
别这样 亲爱的
Come on, hon.

337
00:31:37,356 --> 00:31:39,380
别板着脸不高兴的样子
Don't be so grouchy.

338
00:31:39,791 --> 00:31:41,122
我没有
I'm not...

339
00:31:41,492 --> 00:31:42,686
不高兴
...being grouchy.

340
00:31:42,894 --> 00:31:45,692
我只是想快把书写完
I just want to finish my work.

341
00:31:49,199 --> 00:31:51,599
好的 我明白
Okay. I understand.

342
00:31:51,835 --> 00:31:54,429
我等会再拿些三明治过来
I'll come back later with a couple of sandwiches.

343
00:31:54,638 --> 00:31:57,106
说不定 到时你还能让我看看你写的东西
Maybe you'll let me read something then.

344
00:32:00,309 --> 00:32:01,401
温蒂
Wendy...

345
00:32:01,611 --> 00:32:04,205
我跟你解释一下吧
...let me explain something to you.

346
00:32:05,114 --> 00:32:08,981
你只要进来打岔 就会让我分心
When you come in and interrupt, you're breaking my concentration.

347
00:32:09,184 --> 00:32:10,617
