Back here in Florida, we've got the opposite problem.

560
00:55:22,415 --> 00:55:24,645
温度及湿度都将继续上升
The heat and humidity are supposed to climb.

561
00:55:24,851 --> 00:55:26,819
当地的海滩肯定会人满为患
Local beaches should be jammed.

562
00:55:27,020 --> 00:55:29,044
气象专家 沃尔特.克龙
Our weather expert, Walter Cronice...

563
00:55:29,254 --> 00:55:32,519
等会将会在悠视为大家预测本地天气
will have the local forecast later on Newswatch.

564
01:01:04,121 --> 01:01:08,750
很抱歉 您拨的电话无法接通
We 're sorry. Your call cannot be completed as dialed.

565
01:01:09,091 --> 01:01:12,219
如果需要帮助 请致电接线员
If you need assistance, please call the operator.

566
01:01:29,476 --> 01:01:31,307
是的 是我
Yes, it's me.

567
01:01:31,512 --> 01:01:32,945
谢天谢地
Thank God.

568
01:01:37,617 --> 01:01:39,380
有什么发现么?
Did you find anything?

569
01:01:39,585 --> 01:01:42,315
不 什么都没有
No. Nothing at all.

570
01:01:42,922 --> 01:01:46,084
我他妈鬼影子都没见到一个
I didn't see one goddamn thing.

571
01:01:48,827 --> 01:01:52,319
你去了丹尼说的那个房间? 二三七号?
You went into the room Danny said? To 237?

572
01:01:52,531 --> 01:01:54,088
是的 去过了
Yes, I did.

573
01:01:54,565 --> 01:01:56,362
你什么都没见到?
And you didn't see anything at all?

574
01:01:56,567 --> 01:01:58,558
绝对什么都没有
Absolutely nothing.

575
01:01:58,769 --> 01:02:00,031
他怎么样了?
How is he?

576
01:02:00,237 --> 01:02:02,034
还在睡觉
He's still asleep.

577
01:02:02,440 --> 01:02:03,565
很好
Good.

578
01:02:09,379 --> 01:02:12,473
等他早上睡醒了就会恢复正常的
I'm sure he'll be himself again in the morning.

579
01:02:16,952 --> 01:02:19,443
你确定你去对了房间?
Are you sure it was the right room?

580
01:02:19,655 --> 01:02:22,817
我是说 或许是丹尼搞错了
I mean, maybe Danny made a mistake.

581
01:02:23,024 --> 01:02:25,390
他肯定进了那个房间
He must have gone in that room.

582
01:02:25,593 --> 01:02:28,255
门是开着的 灯也亮着
The door was open, the lights were on.

583
01:02:30,898 --> 01:02:33,229
那我就不明白了
I just don't understand it.

584
01:02:37,571 --> 01:02:40,597
那他身上那些瘀伤是怎么回事呢?
What about those bruises on his neck?

585
01:02:42,775 --> 01:02:45,107
肯定有人伤害了他的
Somebody did that to him.

586
01:02:53,384 --> 01:02:54,817
我想
I think...

587
01:02:56,488 --> 01:02:59,048
是他自己干的
...he did it to himself.

588
01:03:05,062 --> 01:03:06,290
不
No.

589
01:03:06,964 --> 01:03:08,989
不可能
That's not possible.

590
01:03:14,303 --> 01:03:17,966
如果他说的话不是真的
Once you rule out his version of what happened...

591
01:03:18,207 --> 01:03:20,800
那就没别的解释了
...there is no other explanation.

592
01:03:21,276 --> 01:03:22,607
是么?
Is there?

593
01:03:29,183 --> 01:03:32,175
不管是怎么回事
Whatever the explanation is...

594
01:03:35,623 --> 01:03:37,022
我想 我们
...l think we...

595
01:03:37,224 --> 01:03:39,953
都得带丹尼离开这儿
...have to get Danny out of here.

596
01:03:44,731 --> 01:03:46,562
带他离开这儿?
Get him out of here?

597
01:03:50,736 --> 01:03:52,465
你是说
You mean...

598
01:03:53,505 --> 01:03:55,473
离开酒店?
...just leave the hotel?

599
01:04:04,448 --> 01:04:05,914
你们俩真是
It is so...

600
01:04:06,116 --> 01:04:08,550
会在我终于有机会做成点事的时候
...typical of you to create a problem like this...

601
01:04:08,752 --> 01:04:11,277
搞出麻烦来
...when I finally have a chance to accomplish something!

602
01:04:11,488 --> 01:04:14,048
我现在正真正在干事业
When I'm really into my work!

603
01:04:14,257 --> 01:04:18,215
如果我想现在就回去的话 就回得去么?
I could really write my own ticket if I went back now, couldn't l?

604
01:04:18,427 --> 01:04:22,158
开着铲雪当洗车
Shoveling out driveways, work in a car wash.

605
01:04:22,364 --> 01:04:24,456
你觉得怎么样呀?
Any of that appeal to you?

606
01:04:25,667 --> 01:04:28,363
我一直让你把我的生活搞得一团糟
I have let you fuck up my life so far...

607
01:04:28,570 --> 01:04:32,199
不过 这次我不会让你毁了我的
...but I am not going to let you fuck this up.

608
01:05:43,837 --> 01:05:46,135
晚上好 林务局
Good evening. Forest Service.

609
01:05:46,706 --> 01:05:48,139
我叫狄克.哈罗朗
My name is Dick Hallorann.

610
01:05:48,341 --> 01:05:50,774
我是远望酒店的厨师长
I'm the head chef at the Overlook Hotel.

611
01:05:50,976 --> 01:05:53,103
晚上好 有什么能帮到你的么?
Good evening. What can I do for you?

612
01:05:53,312 --> 01:05:56,873
我想打个紧急电话到酒店上去
I've been trying to make an urgent phone call up there...

613
01:05:57,082 --> 01:06:00,380
不过接线员说电话线装已经吹倒了
but the operator said that the phone lines are down.

614
01:06:00,585 --> 01:06:04,180
那附近很多电话线桩都由于暴风雪倒塌了
A lot of lines around here are down due to the storm.

615
01:06:04,389 --> 01:06:07,051
我不想给您造成任何麻烦的
I hate to put you through any trouble...

616
01:06:07,258 --> 01:06:10,488
不过有家人还待在酒店里 而且还有个小孩子
...but there's a family up there all by themselves with a young kid.

617
01:06:10,694 --> 01:06:12,355
就现在这种暴风雪袭击的情况下
And with this storm and everything...

618
01:06:12,562 --> 01:06:15,463
如果你们能用无线电跟他们联系下 我将非常感谢
I'd appreciate it if you'd give them a call on your radio...

619
01:06:15,666 --> 01:06:17,656
就看看他们是不是还好
...just to see if everything's okay.

620
01:06:18,167 --> 01:06:19,464
我很高兴为您致电他们
I'll be glad to do that.

621
01:06:19,669 --> 01:06:22,467
您二十分钟之后再打来好么?
Why don't you call me back in about 20 minutes?

622
01:06:22,672 --> 01:06:24,697
非常感谢 我会的
Thank you very much. I'll do that.

623
01:06:24,907 --> 01:06:26,340
好的 先生
All right, sir.

624
01:06:46,659 --> 01:06:48,627
晚上好 托兰斯先生
Good evening, Mr. Torrance.

625
01:06:48,828 --> 01:06:50,295
晚上好
Good evening.

626
01:07:14,851 --> 01:07:16,318
嗨 劳埃德
Hi, Lloyd.

627
01:07:16,519 --> 01:07:18,384
我刚才走开了 不过现在又回来了
Been away, but now I'm back.

628
01:07:18,655 --> 01:07:20,384
晚上好 托兰斯先生
Good evening, Mr. Torrance.

629
01:07:21,057 --> 01:07:22,046
很高兴见到您
It's good to see you.

630
01:07:22,258 --> 01:07:24,919
回来感觉真好 劳埃德
It's good to be back, Lloyd.

631
01:07:25,561 --> 01:07:27,290
想喝点什么酒 先生?
What'll it be, sir?

632
01:07:28,097 --> 01:07:30,361
给杯能让我一醉方休的
Hair of the dog that bit me.

633
01:07:31,767 --> 01:07:33,427
那就来杯波本威士忌加冰块
Bourbon on the rocks.

634
01:07:34,268 --> 01:07:35,667
就是它了
That'll do her.

635
01:07:49,182 --> 01:07:51,445
免费享用 托兰斯先生
No charge to you, Mr. Torrance.

636
01:07:52,885 --> 01:07:54,853
免费享用?
No charge?

637
01:07:55,488 --> 01:07:57,479
你的钱在这儿派不上用处了
Your money's no good here.

638
01:08:03,128 --> 01:08:04,857
有人帮您付过了
Orders from the house.

639
01:08:08,066 --> 01:08:10,556
有人付过了
Orders from the house.

640
01:08:13,804 --> 01:08:15,795
喝吧 托兰斯先生
Drink up, Mr. Torrance.

641
01:08:18,008 --> 01:08:22,535
我想知道是谁帮我付的帐 劳埃德
I'm the kind of man likes to know who's buying their drinks, Lloyd.

642
01:08:24,847 --> 01:08:27,782
你就不用管这个了 托兰斯先生
It's not a matter that concerns you, Mr. Torrance.

643
01:08:27,984 --> 01:08:29,917
至少 现在不必要知道
At least, not at this point.

644
01:08:34,723 --> 01:08:37,123
你说了算 劳埃德
Anything you say, Lloyd.

645
01:08:37,559 --> 01:08:39,549
你说了算
Anything you say.

646
01:08:52,539 --> 01:08:55,007
噢 天哪 抱歉 先生
Oh, dear! I'm so sorry, sir.

647
01:08:56,109 --> 01:08:57,575
噢 天哪 天哪
Oh, dear. Oh, dear.

648
01:08:57,776 --> 01:09:00,336
看我把你的夹克搞得一团糟 先生
I've made an awful mess of your jacket, sir.

649
01:09:01,580 --> 01:09:05,209
没关系的 我有很多夹克
That's all right. I've got plenty of jackets.

650
01:09:05,417 --> 01:09:08,214
这是荷兰蛋酒 恐怕会留下印迹了
I'm afraid it's advocaat, sir. It tends to stain.

651
01:09:08,419 --> 01:09:09,545
荷兰蛋酒 是么?
Advocaat, is it?

652
01:09:09,754 --> 01:09:11,915
是的 先生 我想最好是
Yes, sir. I think the best thing...

653
01:09:12,123 --> 01:09:14,318
我陪您到男洗手间去
...is to come along to the gentlemen's room...

654
01:09:14,525 --> 01:09:17,049
弄点水洗干净吧 先生
...and we'll get some water to it, sir.

655
01:09:17,894 --> 01:09:21,193
好象你自己身上也弄到了
Looks like you might have got a spot of it on yourself...

656
01:09:21,398 --> 01:09:22,387
侍应老伙计
...Jeevesy old boy.

657
01:09:22,599 --> 01:09:25,761
没关系 先生 您最要紧
That doesn't matter, sir. You're the important one.

658
01:09:26,068 --> 01:09:28,468
你真是个大好人
Awfully nice of you to say.

659
01:09:28,904 --> 01:09:31,771
其实 今晚来参加宴会之前
Of course, I intended to change my jacket this evening...

660
01:09:31,974 --> 01:09:34,238
我就想换到这身衣服的
...before the fish and goose soiree.

661
01:09:34,443 --> 01:09:36,467
非常明智 先生 非常明智
Very wise, sir. Very wise.

662
01:09:36,678 --> 01:09:37,975
好了 我来帮你
Here. I'll just...

663
01:09:38,947 --> 01:09:41,211
把门打开 侍应
...hold this for you there, Jeevesy.

664
01:09:41,416 --> 01:09:43,213
谢谢您 先生 谢谢您
Thank you, sir. Thank you.

665
01:09:44,251 --> 01:09:47,880
看看弄点水是不是能洗得掉
Let's see if we can improve this with a little water, sir.

666
01:09:48,088 --> 01:09:49,350
好吧 我把
All right. I'll just...

667
01:09:49,556 --> 01:09:53,753
波本威士忌和蛋酒都放在这儿
...set my bourbon and advocaat down right there.

668
01:09:54,327 --> 01:09:55,760
一会就好了
Won't keep you a moment.

669
01:09:55,962 --> 01:09:57,361
好的
Fine.

670
01:10:00,433 --> 01:10:02,094
他们都怎么叫你的 侍应
What do they call you, Jeevesy?

671
01:10:02,301 --> 01:10:04,860
格兰蒂 先生 戴伯特.格兰蒂
Grady, sir. Delbert Grady.

672
01:10:09,641 --> 01:10:10,471
格兰蒂?
Grady?

673
01:10:10,675 --> 01:10:12,006
是的 先生
Yes, sir.

674
01:10:13,177 --> 01:10:14,508
戴伯特.格兰蒂
Delbert Grady.

675
01:10:14,712 --> 01:10:16,236
是的 先生
That's right, sir.

676
01:10:24,954 --> 01:10:26,387
格兰蒂先生
Mr. Grady...

677
01:10:27,156 --> 01:10:29,249
我以前在哪儿见过你么?
...haven't I seen you somewhere before?

678
01:10:29,459 --> 01:10:32,154
怎么呢 不 先生 我觉得没见过
Why, no, sir. I don't believe so.

679
01:10:39,201 --> 01:10:41,031
快弄掉了呢 先生
It's coming off now, sir.

680
01:10:45,973 --> 01:10:47,531
格兰蒂先生
Mr. Grady...

681
01:10:49,043 --> 01:10:51,510
你以前是不是做过这儿的看守?
...weren't you once the caretaker here?

682
01:10:51,711 --> 01:10:54,509
怎么 没有呢 先生 没有
Why, no, sir. I don't believe so.

683
01:10:57,550 --> 01:11:00,882
你结婚了 对么 格兰蒂先生
You a married man, are you, Mr. Grady?

684
01:11:01,086 --> 01:11:01,916
是的 先生
Yes, sir.

685
01:11:02,121 --> 01:11:05,386
我有老婆 还有两个女儿
I have a wife and two daughters, sir.

686
01:11:06,425 --> 01:11:07,949
那么
And...

687
01:11:09,627 --> 01:11:10,889
他们现在在哪儿
...where are they now?

688
01:11:11,095 --> 01:11:15,156
就在这附近吧 我现在也不太清楚
They're somewhere around. I'm not quite sure at the moment.

689
01:11:25,842 --> 01:11:28,241
你就说在这儿做过看守
You were the caretaker here.

690
01:11:29,712 --> 01:11:31,703
我认得出你来
I recognize you.

691
01:11:33,082 --> 01:11:36,142
我在报纸上见过你的照片
I saw your picture in the newspapers.

692
01:11:36,585 --> 01:11:38,347
你
You...

693
01:11:38,820 --> 01:11:42,347
把你妻子和女儿都剁成了一块块的
...chopped your wife and daughter up into little bits.

694
01:11:42,857 --> 01:11:44,256
而且
And...

695
01:11:44,893 --> 01:11:46,826
之后你还打爆了自己的脑袋
...then you blew your brains out.

696
01:11:56,736 --> 01:11:58,499
真奇怪 先生
That's strange, sir.

697
01:11:59,505 --> 01:12:02,235
我完全想不起来有这种事
I don't have any recollection of that at all.

698
01:12:05,911 --> 01:12:07,776
格兰蒂先生
Mr. Grady...

699
01:12:08,213 --> 01:12:11,546
你以前确实是这儿的看守
...you were the caretaker here.

700
01:12:19,357 --> 01:12:22,121
很抱歉 不能附和您 先生
I'm sorry to differ with you, sir.

701
01:12:23,994 --> 01:12:25,723
不过 您
But you...

702
01:12:26,463 --> 01:12:28,294
才是看守呀
...are the caretaker.

703
01:12:30,567 --> 01:12:33,467
您一直都是看守
You've always been the caretaker.

704
01:12:36,372 --> 01:12:38,203
我早该知道的 先生
I should know, sir.

705
01:12:39,641 --> 01:12:42,235
我一直都在这儿
I've always been here.

706
01:13:00,460 --> 01:13:02,654
你知道么 托兰斯先生
Did you know, Mr. Torrance...

707
01:13:02,895 --> 01:13:04,658
您的儿子
...that your son...

708
01:13:05,064 --> 01:13:07,760
正准备跟外面的人取得联络
...is attempting to bring an outside party...

709
01:13:07,967 --> 01:13:10,162
对付现在的状况
...into this situation?

710
01:13:12,737 --> 01:13:14,432
你知道么?
Did you know that?

711
01:13:20,677 --> 01:13:22,770
是真的 托兰斯先生
He is, Mr. Torrance.

712
01:13:25,115 --> 01:13:26,275
跟谁?
Who?

713
01:13:28,519 --> 01:13:30,145
跟个黑人
